==English==

===Pronunciation===
*[[w:International Phonetic Alphabet|IPA]]:/di dʒeɪ/
*:Rhymes: [[Rhymes:English:-eɪ|-eɪ]], [[Rhymes:English:-iːdʒeɪ|-iːdʒeɪ]]

===Noun===
'''DJ'''
# A [[disc jockey]].
# A person who plays and [[mix]]es [[music]], usually pre-recorded, at nightclubs, over the radio, and/or as a backup musician for spoken word, or [[hip hop]] performers.

===Verb===
'''to DJ'''
# The act of dj-ing, playing, cutting and mixing/blending music.
[[de:DJ]]